			<div class="blog-faq">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Why is plastic surgery cheaper in India?</h3>
					<p>Plastic surgery costs in India are lower primarily due to lower operational costs, including facility expenses, staff salaries, and overhead. However, this does not mean lower quality. Indian plastic surgeons are highly trained, many with international education and fellowship experience, and use the same advanced technology and techniques found at top clinics worldwide.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is it safe to get plastic surgery in India?</h3>
					<p>Yes, plastic surgery in India is safe when performed by a qualified, board-certified plastic surgeon in an accredited facility. India has numerous internationally accredited hospitals and clinics that adhere to strict safety standards. Choosing a reputable surgeon like Dr. Manoj K Johar ensures that you receive care that meets the highest global standards.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can international patients get plastic surgery in India?</h3>
					<p>Absolutely. India is one of the top destinations for medical tourism, and many clinics, including Dr. Johar's, cater specifically to international patients. Services often include assistance with travel arrangements, accommodation, post-operative care, and follow-up consultations to ensure a smooth experience from start to finish.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What is the most popular plastic surgery procedure in India?</h3>
					<p>Rhinoplasty (nose reshaping) and liposuction are consistently among the most popular procedures, followed by breast augmentation, gynecomastia surgery, and hair transplant. The popularity of specific procedures varies by region and demographic trends.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How do I choose a plastic surgeon in India?</h3>
					<p>Look for a board-certified plastic surgeon with extensive experience in the specific procedure you are considering. Check their qualifications, training, hospital affiliations, before-and-after photos, and patient reviews. Schedule a consultation to discuss your goals and ensure you feel comfortable with the surgeon's approach and communication style.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long should I plan to stay in India for plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>The recommended stay depends on the procedure. Simple procedures may require only a few days, while more complex surgeries like facelifts or abdominoplasty may require two to three weeks to ensure proper initial recovery and follow-up care. Dr. Johar's team can provide a personalized timeline based on your specific procedure.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What are the current trends in plastic surgery in India?</h3>
					<p>Current trends include a significant increase in male patients, growing demand for minimally invasive procedures, rising popularity of combination surgeries, and increasing interest in ethnic-sensitive techniques that enhance features while preserving cultural identity. Medical tourism continues to grow, with patients traveling from across the globe for India's world-class care at competitive prices.</p>
				</div>
